Steps for running a test of the download/parse of package metadata from RHN Hosted.

1. Build this project. 
 mvn compile

2. Run the standalone class, "DownloadPackageMetadataTool"
 Chose either approach "a" or "b"

 a. Use script "downloadMetadata.sh"
  Example: "./downloadMetadata.sh rhel-i386-server-5"
 
 -- OR --

 b. Run through maven as:
 mvn -e exec:java -Dexec.mainClass="org.rhq.enterprise.server.plugins.rhnhosted.xmlrpc.DownloadPackageMetadataTool" -Drhn.channel=$1 -Dexec.args="" -Dlog4j.configuration="file://${PWD}/src/test/resources/test-log4j.xml"

 Change -Drhn.channel= to the channel you want to download metadata for.



